# LoadZone Player PWA

- Treat the player app as mobile-first and token-based, not Clerk-based.
- Keep inputs reachable in the thumb zone and touch targets at least `44x44` (prefer `48x48`).
- Keep each step fast: no more than 3 questions per screen when possible.
- Prefer large rounded controls, clean spacing, and frictionless flows over dense UI.
- Support retries without losing entered data.
- Preserve offline-friendly behavior and avoid unnecessary dependence on live round-trips.
- Be careful with public endpoints: validate token access, sanitize input ranges, and avoid leaking
  token values in logs or UI.
- Push notification and service worker flows should degrade gracefully when unsupported.
